                <p>
                  Digital signature is a form of electronic signature that uses
                  cryptographic methods to mark the validity of a digital
                  document. Digital signature does not mean a physical signature
                  that is scanned or drawn on a computer and then pasted on a
                  document, but rather a mathematical calculation using the
                  concept of public key cryptography on digitally signed data.
                  There are two activities in the digital signature concept:
                </p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Sign</strong>, i.e. the activity of affixing digital
                    signatures to documents.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Verify</strong>, i.e. the activity of determining
                    whether the digital signature on a document is valid.
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <br />

                <p>
                  The following is the purpose of applying a digital signature
                  to a document which is the benefit of public key cryptography:
                </p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Otentikasi</strong>, i.e. ensuring that the document
                    is indeed signed by a valid signatory. Only the owner of
                    certain signatures can affix his signature to the document.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Integritas</strong>, i.e. ensuring that the document
                    is not altered once it is signed. If the document is
                    modified in the slightest, the digital signature will
                    automatically become invalid.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Non-repudiasi</strong>, i.e. ensuring that the
                    signer cannot deny that he has signed a document.
                  </li>
                </ul>
